# Tugobo AI - Stack Conventions

## Database
- ALWAYS use Drizzle ORM. Never write raw SQL in application code.
- All queries go through `@tugobo/db` package. Never import `postgres` or `@supabase/supabase-js` directly in `apps/web` route handlers for DB work.
- Every business table MUST have a `hotel_id` column (multi-tenant from day 1).
- Use `db.insert().returning()` to get back inserted rows.

## Channels
- NEVER call Twilio or Meta APIs directly from route handlers or agents.
- ALL channel interactions go through `packages/channels/` adapters.
- The adapter interface is `ChannelAdapter` in `packages/channels/src/types.ts`.

## Agent Tools
- ALL side-effects (DB writes, external API calls, sending messages) performed by agents go through typed tool functions in `packages/core/src/tools/`.
- Tool functions are passed to the AI SDK `tools` parameter. They are never called directly by agent code.

## Workflows
- ALL durable, multi-step agent work goes through Inngest functions defined in `packages/core/src/graph/`.
- Never use `setTimeout` or raw `setInterval` for retry logic.

## Prompts
- ALL system prompts live in `packages/core/src/prompts/index.ts`.
- Prompts are versioned (e.g. `_v1`, `_v2`). Never edit a live prompt in-place; create a new version.

## Security
- NEVER log phone numbers. Use `[REDACTED]` via the logger in `packages/shared/src/logger.ts`.
- NEVER log message bodies.
- ALWAYS validate Twilio webhook signatures before processing.
- NEVER commit real keys. Use `.env.local` (git-ignored).

## TypeScript
- `strict: true` always.
- No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow with Zod.
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for data shapes. Use `interface` only for objects that will be implemented/extended.
